          "لِبْدَ سَرْجِهِ": "the felt covering of his saddle, from which dust may be taken",
          "فَيَتَيَمَّمُ": "he performs tayammum, the dry ablution",
          "غُبَارِهِ": "its dust, used as the material for tayammum",
          "الطِّينَ": "clay, permitted here when nothing else is available",
          "فَلَا بَأْسَ": "there is no harm; an expression of legal permissibility"
        }
